yt_dlp.title: Bryan Sutton Flatpicking "Whiskey Before Breakfast"
yt_dlp.description:
Get FREE lessons from Bryan Sutton and others here: https://tfir.es/AWFreeLessons

EXPLORE All Our Schools: https://tfir.es/48AnINc
SUBSCRIBE to ArtistWorks on YouTube for more videos: https://tfir.es/AWYouTube

Bryan Sutton (http://artistworks.com/bryan-sutton) is in the ArtistWorks Studio in Napa, CA this week recording more guitar lessons for all his online guitar students. Here he is demonstrating some of the best flatpicking guitar skills around on the classic bluegrass song, "Whiskey Before Breakfast", which happens to be a featured topic in his new guitar lessons, coming soon! 

There is a lot of new and exciting stuff coming soon to the Online Bluegrass Guitar School with Bryan Sutton so stay tuned....

If you have not already, be sure to visit the link for more information about Bryan's online guitar school, which includes some free sample lessons. Students have unlimited access to all of Bryan's in depth guitar curriculum - covering all aspects of bluegrass guitar and flatpicking from beginner to advanced. 

All of Bryan's students can also submit their own videos of themselves playing directly to Bryan for his personal review. He will watch your practice video and then respond with his own video where he will let you know what you should focus on in order to improve.  Bryan's response video gets paired together with the student submission and made available for all of his online students to see. So as a student, you can watch all the Video Exchanges™ that Bryan has recorded - which there are hundreds of and more being recorded all the time! You never know, the advice he gives someone else might just apply to you too.  For more information on how Video Exchange™ learning works visit http://artistworks.com.

Bryan Sutton is an undisputed master of flatpicking and aside from his solo career is a sought out Nashville session player and also plays guitar in the legendary bluegrass band Hot Rize.
